<subSubSection lastPageId="55" lastPageNumber="56" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="54.[151,1436,1779,2019]" lastBlockId="55.[151,1435,151,212]" lastPageId="55" lastPageNumber="56" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[203,339,1958,1983]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" reason="1">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[346,542,1959,1983]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Liriomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helenii">
<emphasis box="[346,542,1959,1983]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Liriomyza helenii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is relatively variable in external colouration and should only be considered reliably identified after the male terminalia have been examined—the surstylus has two subapical spines, the ejaculatory apodeme has a long, narrow stalk and a reduced triangular blade, a small cup-like distiphallus basally compressed in lateral view and an apically (not ventrally) directed paraphallus.
</paragraph>
